useful commands in nano
M-A - Mark text from current position. To end selection ^K or M-6
M-^ - Copy text to buffer- current line or whatever was selected (works after pressing second time)
^K - Cut text to buffer - current line or whatever was marked with M-A
^U - Paste text from buffer, which copied or cut
^R - Insert text from another file
^W - Search for text
M-R - Search for text and replace it
^C - Current position
M-C - Current position constantly visible
M-L - Long line wrapping enable/disable
M-$ - Soft line wrapping enable / disable
M-G - Go to line number and column number
^O - Save file
^X - exit nano while optionally saving a file

